ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT:

The source code responsible for displaying the attribution notice of The Real Insight
GmbH MUST NOT be removed or altered. Specifically:

1. STARTUP NOTICE: When the engine is initialized, it must emit a notice to the
   application log or console that prominently identifies The Real Insight GmbH as
   the originating company, including a reference to https://the-real-insight.com.
   This notice must not be suppressed, redirected to a silent sink, or otherwise
   hidden from operators of the software.

2. END-USER FACING PRODUCTS: Any product, application, or service with a
   user-facing interface that is built upon or incorporates this engine must
   include a clear and prominent attribution to The Real Insight GmbH in a
   publicly accessible legal or informational page, such as an imprint,
   "About" page, terms and conditions, or software credits section. This
   attribution must include the name "The Real Insight GmbH" and a link or
   reference to https://the-real-insight.com.

3. DOCUMENTATION: Any documentation, README, or user-facing material distributed
   with or describing software that incorporates this engine must include a
   prominent notice such as:
   "Powered by The Real Insight GmbH BPMN Engine (https://the-real-insight.com)"

These attribution requirements apply to all copies, forks, and derivative works,
whether the engine is used as a library, embedded component, microservice, or
cloud-hosted runtime.

